The Labour Ministry is calling for transparency regarding business relief measures.Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The labour ministry is calling for transparency regarding business relief measures. Minister Thulas Nxesi wants employers to help their workers using funds from the UIF. READ: COVID-19: SA in recovery for rest of 2020 - Kubayi-Ngubane "Employers must be honest. There are challenges where employers are not assisting employees to claim. Some 220,000 entitled to claim have not yet done so. We are endeavouring now to contact those individuals." The lockdown has left many without jobs. Economic recovery plans to deal with the impact of COVID-19 will be in place until the end of the year. The country's already fragile economy has been strained to unprecedented levels. Courtesy #DStv403 Nxesi, says workers can't take the fall for their employers' mistakes. He's appealing to companies to make sure they seek funding through the right channels. READ: SA's recovery will take a great deal of effort and resources: Ramaphosa Many people are suffering because they are unable to work during the national lockdown. Watch the video above for more on this story.